message.content:
Below is one coherent way to “read” these two little tower‐like assemblies and match them (as closely as possible) to the blocks in the second “dictionary” image.  Note that the circular “ring” pieces (the blue one on the left tower and the red one on the right tower) must each be composed from the red “C‐shaped” halves (#3 and #4) in the dictionary, since there is no single ready‐made ring block.  Likewise, the small orange “roof” pieces are made by choosing the appropriate orange wedge(s) (#11–#16) in the orientation that matches the slopes you see in the target.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  DESCRIBE THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
■  There are TWO separate structures:

A)  LEFT STRUCTURE (cylindrical tower with blue band):
   •  Total of 6 major “pieces” visible:
       –  One tall orange cylinder in the middle.  
       –  A square “band” around its midpoint in blue (appears as a ring).  
       –  Four orange wedges/facets that meet that blue band at the base.  
       –  A small orange wedge “cap” on top.  
   •  Conceptually this is 2 layers high:
       –  Bottom layer is the cylinder plus the blue band+wedges.  
       –  Second (top) layer is the single orange wedge “cap.”  

B)  RIGHT STRUCTURE (“rocket” shape with a circular opening):
   •  Total of 8 visible blocks if you count each wedge and cube separately:
       –  One red ring in the center at the bottom (the big circular opening).  
       –  Two yellow cubes, one on each bottom corner.  
       –  A green cube and a blue cube stacked above the red ring (forming the middle layer).  
       –  Two orange wedges flanking the ring on left/right (they form the rocket’s slanted sides).  
       –  One or two orange wedges at the very top forming the pointed “roof.”  
   •  You can think of it as 3 layers:
       –  Bottom: red ring + two yellow cubes + (the lower portion of the orange side wedges).  
       –  Middle: green and blue cubes in the center, sides of the orange wedges.  
       –  Top: the final orange wedge(s) making the “nose cone.”  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECT BLOCKS FROM THE DICTIONARY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below is one way to match each visible piece to the provided block indices (remember, no re‐coloring or re‐orienting beyond what’s shown):

A)  For the LEFT STRUCTURE:
   •  Orange cylinder → Block #10 (used once).  
   •  Blue “ring” → assemble it from two red C‐shaped blocks (#3 and #4) is not correct color, 
     so strictly speaking there is no exact blue ring block in the dictionary.  
     (Hence this structure cannot be perfectly reproduced from the provided blocks—no blue 
      piece matches that shape/orientation.)  
   •  Orange wedges around the band and on top → any of #11–#16 that have their slope 
     oriented the same way seen in the picture (most likely #11 or #12, repeated several times).  

B)  For the RIGHT STRUCTURE (“rocket”):
   •  Red ring with circular opening → combine blocks #3 and #4 (each is a half‐cylindrical 
     cutout, mirrored).  Put them together so the circular hole faces front.  
   •  Two Yellow cubes → Block #7 (used twice).  
   •  One Green cube → Block #6.  
   •  One Blue cube → Block #5.  
   •  Orange wedges (the slanted sides and the top “roof”) → choose from #11–#16 according 
     to how the slopes run.  Often #12 or #15 work for a “roof peak” if placed in pairs.  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  PROPOSED ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below is a sample build sequence for assembling just the “rocket” on the right (the only one 
we can fully match using #3+#4 for the ring).  In practice, you would add the orange wedges 
in whatever order is easiest—this is just one notional example:

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 3   (place first half of red ring)
  Step2:  Move block with index 4   (complete the red ring)
  Step3:  Move block with index 7   (left yellow cube at the base)
  Step4:  Move block with index 7   (right yellow cube at the base)
  Step5:  Move block with index 6   (green cube on top of ring, left side)
  Step6:  Move block with index 5   (blue cube on top of ring, right side)
  Step7:  Move block with index 12  (orange wedge on left side)
  Step8:  Move block with index 12  (orange wedge on right side)
  Step9:  Move block with index 15  (one half of the top roof wedge)
  Step10: Move block with index 15  (second half of the top roof wedge)
}

You would follow a similar idea for the left tower, but since the dictionary does not contain 
a blue ring of that shape and color, it cannot be perfectly replicated from these blocks.
